# Project Architecture

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 14+ (App Router) with TypeScript (strict mode)
- Material UI (MUI) v6 + MUI X Charts
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage)
- axe-core + Puppeteer for automated accessibility scanning

## Folder structure

- `config/` — app-specific configuration (audit scopes, WCAG criteria, technology options). Suffix: `.config.ts`
- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `src/components/` — UI components following Atomic Design (atoms, molecules, organisms)
- `src/utils/` — pure, reusable functions (no React, no side effects). Suffix: `.util.ts`
- `src/hooks/` — custom React hooks grouped by logical domain. Suffix: `.hooks.ts`
- `src/contexts/` — React Context providers + consumer hooks. Suffix: `Context.tsx`
- `src/types/` — shared TypeScript interfaces and type definitions
- `src/lib/` — third-party integrations (Supabase client, axe-core scanner)
- `supabase/migrations/` — SQL migration files for database schema

## Components (Atomic Design)

- `atoms/` — smallest building blocks (StatusBadge, PriorityChip, ConformanceIcon, WcagLevelBadge)
- `molecules/` — compositions of atoms (CriterionCard, SamplePageRow, IssueCard, FindingForm, ScreenshotUploader)
- `organisms/` — full sections with business logic (AuditWizard, ReportingPanel, DashboardCharts, ScanResultsTable)

## Key rules

- No `.find()` or `.filter()` calls in components — extract to utils or hooks
- No prop drilling — use Context + custom hooks for shared state
- No magic numbers — use named constants from `config/audit.config.ts` or `config/wcag.config.ts`
- Pages are lazy-loaded via `React.lazy()` with a `Suspense` fallback
- All Supabase queries go through hooks in `src/hooks/`, never called directly in components
- API routes in `src/app/api/` handle server-side logic (scanning, AI, screenshots)
